	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>30 October 5619</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I avail myself<lb/> of <persName>Mrs Cohen&#39;s</persName> return to <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> to send you for</p>
				<table rows="8" cols="3">
				<row>
				<cell>2 Daily Prayers</cell>
				<cell>&#64; 2.50</cell>
				<cell>&#36;5.</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>1 Kipoor do</cell>
				<cell>&#45;5&#45;</cell>
				<cell>5.</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>1 set do</cell>
				<cell>&#45;23 37</cell>
				<cell><hi rend="underline">23.37</hi></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				<cell>33.37</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>less 20&#37; commission</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell><hi rend="underline">6.67</hi></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				<cell>26.70</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>1 Eng. Bible <persName>Miss S Joseph</persName></cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell><hi rend="underline">  4</hi></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				<cell><hi rend="underline">&#36;30.70</hi></cell>
				</row>
				</table>
				<p>Thirty dollars seventy cents in all<lb/> including the usual commission<lb/> allowed me by my father for the<lb/> sale of his Edition.  I have not<lb/> yet received the amount of any<lb/> of the above except the Bible<lb/> but I would not trust the Post</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>and <persName>Mrs Cohen</persName> saves you 50 or<lb/> 75 cents express.  I regret I<lb/> cannot forward you any Occident<lb/> subscriptions&#8212;people are not<lb/> over ready to pay these&#44; or their<lb/> dues for books.  The Bible had<lb/> been paid for some time&#44; but<lb/> I waited to forward so small<lb/> an amount.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am obliged to you for<lb/> your congratulations on my having<lb/> received a title and a third son<lb/> the <add>Hebrew</add> I trust and pray.<lb/>  I did not send the article to the<lb/> Messenger but some friends or<lb/> the Editor wrote it.  I am not<lb/> a correspondent of that most<lb/> creditable sheet&#44; and truth<lb/> I am not quite Miss nancified<add>&#63;</add><lb/> yet.</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>I could not yet speak to<lb/> <persName>Miss John Levey</persName> about the prayer<lb/> Books&#44; but will do so at an<lb/> early opportunity.  She has been<lb/> sick.  <persName>John Levey</persName> did <hi rend="underline">not</hi> die a<lb/> rich man.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">They are about establishing<lb/> a Polish or German Synagogue<lb/> here <add>Hebrew</add>.  The<lb/> members are a nice lot&#8212;what<lb/> <persName>Charles Dickens</persName> would call<lb/> very pretty young man for<lb/> a nice tea party.  I may&#44; perhaps<lb/> write you more of this anon.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I do not know whether I<lb/> have charged correctly for the<lb/> Daily Prayers.  I paid one dollar<lb/> 25 cents express charges for<lb/> <persName>Rogauds</persName> Books &#38; Occidents</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>Please let me know whether I<lb/> am to charge it to him.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With best wishes I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
		</body>
	</text>
